%% Diagram: Per-author undo with stack rewriting
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant CA as Client A
    participant MP as Server (Rust)
    participant CB as Client B

    Note over CA: A1: set fill = red
    CA->>MP: delta(O.fill=red, seq 10)
    MP-->>CB: broadcast

    Note over CB: B1: set stroke = blue
    CB->>MP: delta(O.stroke=blue, seq 11)
    MP-->>CA: broadcast

    Note over CA: A1 pushed to A's undo stack.<br/>B1 lives on B's stack only.

    Note over CA: A presses Undo
    CA->>CA: pop A1, inverse fill=gray
    CA->>MP: delta(O.fill=gray, seq 12)
    Note over CA: Rewrite A's redo stack at undo time:<br/>later Redo only re-asserts A's edits.
    MP-->>CB: broadcast

    Note over CA: A presses Redo
    CA->>CA: pop redo (red), rewrite undo stack
    CA->>MP: delta(O.fill=red, seq 13)
    MP-->>CB: broadcast

    Note over CA,CB: Invariant: undo → copy → redo<br/>leaves the document unchanged.
